.TH PATHSET "1" "April 2026" "pathset 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pathset \- manage your shell PATH from a config file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pathset
[\fI\,-c CONFIG\/\fR] [\fI\,-k KIND\/\fR] [\fI\,-d\/\fR] [\fI\,-q\/\fR] [\fI\,-v\/\fR] [\fI\,-V\/\fR] [\fI\,-h\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads a list of directories from a config file and prints a ':'\-joined
string to stdout. Compose into any variable with $(...):
.IP
export PATH="$(pathset \fB\-q\fR \fB\-d\fR)"
export MANPATH="$(pathset \fB\-k\fR man \fB\-q\fR \fB\-d\fR)"
export INFOPATH="$(pathset \fB\-k\fR info \fB\-q\fR \fB\-d\fR)"
fpath=( ${(s.:.)$(pathset \fB\-k\fR fpath \fB\-q\fR \fB\-d\fR)} )   # zsh array
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR CONFIG
read config from CONFIG (overrides default lookup)
.TP
\fB\-k\fR KIND
select kind: path (default), man, info, fpath
.TP
\fB\-d\fR
drop duplicate entries (first occurrence wins)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR
suppress skip warnings on stderr
.TP
\fB\-v\fR
print kept entries and expansions on stderr (\fB\-q\fR wins)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR
print version and exit
.TP
\fB\-h\fR
show this help and exit
.SS "Config file syntax:"
.IP
\- one directory per line, in priority order
\- lines whose first non\-whitespace character is '#' are comments
.IP
(full\-line only; '#' mid\-path is data, not a comment)
.IP
\- blank lines are ignored; CRLF line endings are tolerated
\- entries that don't exist or are empty directories are skipped
\- prefix an entry with '?' to mark it optional (silent skip,
.IP
no exit\-code effect): e.g. `?/opt/homebrew/bin`
.SS "Expansion (applied per entry, before the directory check):"
.TP
\fI\,~/foo\/\fP
\fI\,$HOME/foo\/\fP            (only at start of entry)
.TP
~user/foo
that user's home + \fI\,/foo\/\fP (via getpwnam)
.TP
\fI\,$VAR/foo\/\fP
\fI\,$VAR/foo\/\fP             (no expansion if unset \-> skip)
.TP
${VAR}/foo
braced form, useful next to a name char
.IP
Not supported: mid\-string '~', ${VAR:\-default}, '\e$' escapes.
.SS "Config lookup (first match wins; <kind> = path|man|info|fpath):"
.IP
1. \fB\-c\fR CONFIG (no fallback if missing ??? fatal error)
2. $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/pathset/<kind> (only if XDG_CONFIG_HOME is set)
3. $HOME/.config/pathset/<kind>    (XDG default ??? canonical)
4. $HOME/.pathset/<kind>           (legacy home location)
.SS "Shell setup (add to your shell rc):"
.TP
zsh / bash:
export PATH="$(pathset \fB\-q\fR \fB\-d\fR)"
.TP
fish:
set \fB\-gx\fR PATH (pathset \fB\-q\fR \fB\-d\fR | string split :)
.SS "Exit codes:"
.TP
0
every config entry was emitted
.TP
1
fatal error (missing config, I/O error, out of memory)
.TP
2
bad command\-line argument
.TP
3
one or more entries were skipped (expand or filter failure;
\&'?optional' skips and dedup drops do NOT contribute)
